Changes in attachCellRenderer AG-746 break aurelia renderers

Aurelia returns document fragments - previously it would have been folded into:

this.eParentOfValue.appendChild(this.cellRendererGui);

But now due to the type checks it falls into:

this.eParentOfValue.innerHTML = (<any>this.cellRendererGui).toString() + '';
this.cellRendererGui = <HTMLElement> this.eParentOfValue.firstChild;

This results in a toString from an html element - ie [object DocumentFragment]

Editor and Pinned Row examples demonstrate this

typeof the document fragment is an object, but isnt an instance of HTMLElement - if it was this would work

For non-simple pivots (with more than one level of pivoting) you cannot set pinned row data for pivotted data

Taking javascript-grid-pivoting/examplePivot.js as an example, if you add:

{code:javascript}
    onGridReady() {
        gridOptions.api.setPinnedBottomRowData([{
            'pivot_2': 'p',
            // 'gold': 'g' // this works
        }])
    }
{code}

Where 'pivot_2' is the colId of the first aggregated pivot column - this doesnt do anything, but setting 'gold' works, but this will set the value across all applicable columns, not just the specific one you may want to set

